# rucio-no-opa-policy

Phase 1 Rucio policy package тАФ Rucio as PDP, all permission logic inline in Python.

---

## What it enforces

**Protocol combos** тАФ TPC transfer paths verified with Rucio/FTS maintainers.
The destination storage initiates TPC by pulling from the source тАФ S3 cannot
act as a TPC destination.
See [Transfer Scenarios Overview](../docs/transfer-scenarios-overview.md) for the full matrix.

| Source | Destination | Allowed |
|--------|-------------|---------|
| WebDAV | WebDAV | тЬУ TPC native |
| S3 | WebDAV | тЬУ WebDAV pulls from S3 |
| XrdHTTP | WebDAV | тЬУ WebDAV pulls from XrdHTTP |
| S3 | XrdHTTP | тЬУ XrdHTTP pulls from S3 |
| XrdHTTP | XrdHTTP | тЬУ Native HTTP TPC |
| WebDAV | S3 | тЬЧ S3 cannot act as TPC destination |
| XrdHTTP | S3 | тЬЧ S3 cannot act as TPC destination |
| S3 | S3 | тЬЧ Neither side supports TPC pull |

**RSE naming** тАФ must match `<SITE>_<TYPE>` where TYPE тИИ
`{DATADISK, SCRATCHDISK, LOCALGROUPDISK, TAPE, USERDISK}`.

Examples: `CERN_DATADISK` тЬУ ┬╖ `BNL_TAPE` тЬУ ┬╖ `cern_datadisk` тЬЧ ┬╖ `CERN_UNKNOWN` тЬЧ

**Actions with custom logic** (all others fall back to root-or-admin):

| Action | Extra check |
|--------|-------------|
| `add_rule` | Protocol combo + RSE naming + account ownership |
| `add_rse` | Privileged + RSE naming convention |
| `update_rse` | Privileged + RSE naming on rename |

**Domain rules run before privilege checks** тАФ even root cannot register
`cern_bad` as an RSE or push an S3тЖТS3 transfer.

---

## Install

```bash
python3 -m pip install -e phase1-no-opa/
```

## Configure Rucio

```ini
# rucio.cfg
[policy]
package = rucio_no_opa_policy
```

---

## Running the tests

```bash
python3 -m pip install pytest -e phase1-no-opa/
python3 -m pytest tests/test_phase1_rules.py tests/test_phase1_permission.py tests/test_phase1_e2e_scenarios.py -v
```

| File | Tests | What it covers |
|------|-------|----------------|
| `test_phase1_rules.py` | 35 | Pure domain logic тАФ protocol combos, RSE naming, kwargs validation |
| `test_phase1_permission.py` | 21 | `has_permission()` dispatch, all covered actions |
| `test_phase1_e2e_scenarios.py` | 30 | Scenario tests: flowchart allow/deny paths |
